Head and pronotum with pronounced isodiametric microsculpture and with extremely fine, barely noticeable sparse punctation. Pronotum approximately 1.8 times as broad as long and 1.4 times as broad as head, posterior margin very finely margined (visible only at a magnification of 100 x). Elytra approximately 1.9 times as long as pronotum; interstices without microsculpture. Process of mesoventrite with a moderately pronounced median keel (
Fig. 12
